
# head: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# - type: feat, build, ci, docs, perf, refactor, style, test, revert, merge. MUST be one of them, lower case English.
#   - feat: build a new feature
#   - fix: fix a bug
#   - refactor: refactory code
#   - build: Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies (example scopes: gradle, deps)
#   - test: add/fix unit test
#   - perf: code change for enhancing performance
#   - revert: revert some commits
#   - merge: merge another branch. not recommand to merge another branch.
#   - ci: Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts (example scopes: helm, gitlab)
#   - docs: add readme or something like this.
#   - style: code style
# - scope: business/configration/entity name, can be empty (eg. if the change is a global or difficult to assign to a single component). CAN be Chinese.
# - subject: MUST start with lowercase and persent tense verb (such as 'change'), 100-character line. MUST NOT use dot(.) at the end. CAN be Chinese.
#
# body: [OPTIONAL] 72-character wrapped. start with imperative, present tense verb, CAN be Chinese. This should answer:
# * Why was this change necessary?
# * How does it address the problem?
# * Are there any side effects?
#
# footer: [OPTIONAL]
# - Contain any information about Breaking Changes and also the place to reference GitHub/Gitlab issues that this commit Closes.
# - BREAKING CHANGE
# - Closes issues: #issueId
